WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified memory profile for the JEDEC LPDDR6 and LPDDR6X standards.
It defines the data rate (10.7–14.4 Gbps per pin), the channel
architecture (48 bits per channel, 16-bit per sub-channel, quad-channel),
the bandwidth formula, the power efficiency (21% over LPDDR5), and the
maximum capacity (512 GB via SOCAMM2 modules).

WHY IT EXISTS
LPDDR6 is the memory backbone of 2026 flagship smartphones (Snapdragon
8 Elite Gen 5, A19 Pro, Dimensity 9500) and is extending into AI
datacenters via SOCAMM2 and PIM (Processing-in-Memory). GIOP must model
its bandwidth and capacity as formulas to predict frame buffer transfer
times and AI model loading latency.

HOW IT WORKS
Data Rate:
  LPDDR6: 10.7 Gbps to 14.4 Gbps per pin (JEDEC standard upper limit).
  LPDDR6X: 12.8 Gbps (Samsung), targeting 14.0 Gbps.[reference:29]

Bandwidth per Package:
  BW_package = (pins_per_channel * f_data * 2(DDR)) / 8 (bytes)
  For a 48-bit channel at 14.4 Gbps:
    BW_channel = (48 * 14.4e9 * 2) / 8 = 172.8 GB/s
  For a quad-channel package (192-bit total):
    BW_package = 4 * 172.8 = 691.2 GB/s (peak theoretical).
  Typical smartphone (64-bit): BW_device = 86.4 GB/s (14.4 Gbps × 64 bits).
  [reference:30]

Capacity:
  Single die: 16 Gb (2 GB) at 14.4 Gbps (SK Hynix, ISSCC 2026).
  Max package capacity: up to 512 GB via stacked dies and SOCAMM2 modules
  for AI datacenter applications.[reference:31]

Power Efficiency:
  P_ddr = V_dd * I_dd + P_termination
  V_dd = 1.05 V (LPDDR6) vs 1.1 V (LPDDR5), I_dd scales with f_data.
  Active power: P_active = C_load * V_dd^2 * f_data * utilization
  Power efficiency: 21% improvement over LPDDR5 at equivalent bandwidth.
  Self-refresh power: <0.5 mW per Gb.

Processing-in-Memory (PIM):
  LPDDR6 introduces PIM standard, where simple operations (ADD, MUL,
  MAC) are performed directly in the memory bank, reducing data movement
  for AI inference by up to 60%. GIOP can target PIM-enabled LPDDR6 for
  neural network inference at the memory controller level.[reference:32]

Latency:
  t_RCD (RAS-to-CAS delay): ~18 ns
  t_CL (CAS latency): ~22 ns at 14.4 Gbps
  t_RP (precharge): ~18 ns
  Effective first-word latency: (t_RCD + t_CL) * 1/f = ~40 ns.
  Sustained read throughput reaches ~90% of peak BW for sequential access.

WHERE IT IS DEPLOYED
- 2026 flagship smartphones (Snapdragon 8 Elite Gen 5, A19 Pro, Dimensity
  9500, Exynos 2600).
- AI datacenters (SOCAMM2 modules with PIM).
- GIOP on-device AI inference, real-time HDR video encoding.

WHO USES IT
L1 Architects designing memory-bound GIOP transforms; L2 Engineers
optimizing frame buffer transfer scheduling.

WHAT PROBLEM IT SOLVES
Replaces "faster memory" with the exact bandwidth formula, PIM capability
model, and power consumption curve, enabling GIOP to predict whether a
workload (e.g., 8K HDR neural denoising) will be memory-bandwidth-limited
or compute-limited on a given device.

